Daily menu of an obese child: no embedded breakfast and dinner
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 have overweight problems, with overweight affecting 9% of the school population and obesity at 5%.
Obese children mostly come from families with a lifestyle that is unhealthy, according to current research.
It is again demonstrated the importance of the environment where it grows for the healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as reference.
At the table, obsessed children are fed, for example, of embedded at least twice as often as children of families with normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of the obese had eaten fries the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program “Obesity is not a coincidence.”
In overweight families, there is no habit of sporting, which is applicable to most current families, where only 15% of children answered that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
A survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and nearly 900 basic education children from all over the Czech Republic participated in the same survey.
It was already the second edition of the program "Obesity is not a coincidence", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the Unilever company.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from 4th to 8th grade.
A proper diet and plenty of exercise in the family are decisive factors, which make the number of overweight and even obese children noticeably decrease.
“Only half of the children surveyed answered that they have five meals per day according to the diet: breakfast, lunch, lunch, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet,” says one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast but with built-in for dinner
Experts warn that, in a healthy development, it is also important the details, which also count, such as having a fixed time for breakfast with the family.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of schoolchildren’s families eat breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one eats breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to find out that in 10% of households you don’t eat anything.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a proper daily diet.
The study shows that in families of obese children, insanity potatoes are consumed much more often.
Almost everyone – regardless of weight – drinks sweet refreshments daily (70%).
Usually, more than 40% of children surveyed do sports, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Make your diet.
The next phase of the study made it possible for the chosen chicks (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The dietary preferences of Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15, from the point of view of a healthy diet, are far from ideal."
Among their favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
“It’s especially alarming the popularity of sweet refreshments,” the study’s final report warns.
The main food is the palm, the pasta, and the poultry meat is closely followed.
Practically, children always reject legumes and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Changing to Healthy Habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive the right information.
“In the control group of study participants, who filled out the questionnaire after completing the prevention program ‘Obesity is not a coincidence’, there was in many cases a significant change in favor of the principles of healthy eating,” the study’s findings pointed out.
It draws attention, for example, to the sweet refreshments, where many children would start to prefer normal and current water.
Children would also more often choose bird meat and fish for the main meal in the questionnaire and restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
