In Need for Speed: The Run competes all over America.
Reveal
A trip, in principle careless, is complicated due to a series of improper carelessness of a routine trip during the morning shift.
To a certain extent it was able to meet expectations, but this is of no use, if, in fact, it was not intended to do anything extraordinary.
The new release, which adds to the title, aroused great expectations already before its premiere.
He promised that he would give new air to the old racing saga Need for Speed and, as a result of what is shown, it appears as a game that should not end up being a genre of action without more.
We also feel curious about how the inserted scenes would be, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As is usually the case in NFS series, the results did not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be given as acceptable, but in total points are lost due to absurd failures, which have already appeared in the series for years.
In reality, errors cannot be called errors, but rather the incomprehensible debugging of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
It introduces you to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit at the steering wheel on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
From this it is deduced that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
In this way, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even eye-catching, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to the previous deliveries of the series.
Therefore, it is nothing of the other world.
But walking through the desert, the autumn landscape or the snow-covered high mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
Thus, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
Instead, in the mountains you have to be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to advance to a required number of rivals (normal in a classic race), then you try to win time (chronometered classic duel) and then await a duel against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this sometimes the police appears, which does nothing but make things even more difficult.
What’s new is the scenery outside the car.
There are interactive animations when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than you would expect (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the footprints of the previous episodes.
That means that to this day it is no longer a great thing, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you can already search elsewhere.
But a race designed with quite a lot of action suits this driving style quite well, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, everything's in order.
But the problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the right driving models, the same is no longer the case with collisions.
Of games like this you can’t expect to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a blow to any object, you can’t predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It’s typical that, by making a very adjusted advance or circulating the car with normal traffic, there are only slight rocks, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing uncontrollable pirouettes.
It even ends up totally destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no major problems arise, but it can put them in a bad mood.
The resets are scheduled in such a way that, when you have an accident or leave the track, the game returns you to the last point of rescue on the track.
However, in each race there are only five resets available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it’s only a help in case something goes wrong, but it’s not very reliable.
Sometimes, even resetting helps, only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A big disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find yourself somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same setup, even if you're the first, fifth, or you arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes you especially angry in situations, when you see that two cars going to the meeting in opposite directions, your opponent moves smoothly, but when you arrive, you have to turn or brake.
It’s the same when you arrive, because it’s programmed because the “surprise” will always happen in front of your nose.
Opponents also have another advantage.
Throughout the game you will reach sites where, regardless of the moment, the same opponent will always go ahead of you in the same place.
In addition, this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming in front of you, so at first you can papillate the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it will certainly disappoint you right away.
And it is a shame, because even though the model of the journey is simple, the game is fun and action, so it is often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn’t matter if the merit is taken the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or the race ranking so that boredom doesn’t fit, or anything else.
An unusual idea is to change cars during races.
You have to pay attention to gasoline suppliers next to the road, because that’s where you have to change your car, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough of what you have.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight motorways and supersportive exotics for technical driving, for example, by mountain roads with curves.
In addition, the main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know through the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog feature is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community features.
One of the hardest elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
By car you reach the metro tunnel (pass), where you start running in the dark on the paths (pass).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, behind you arrives the metro convoy and takes you forward without further ado.
In the writing we will certainly have a discussion about this for several days, whether during the programming of the game no one even thought a little or whether the authors really take us for a bunch of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even superb.
What a shame that in the most tense moments the image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This especially affects accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
Audio is good and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to be pleasing to most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game for their music alone.
The final feel of Need for Speed: The Run is quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely stupid mistakes, we would have trouble affirming that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not finished.
Fun is guaranteed, but be prepared because mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the strength of an airport reflector.
The choirs of the University of Carolina will participate in the concert "Students of Terciopelo".
