Unskilled immigrants work in sectors that do not attract national workers and the most skilled in dynamic sectors where training does not meet the demand for staff.
Positive impact on salaries
Just as a surgeon would have difficulty working in a country that lacks anesthesia, complementarity between nationals and immigrants causes the arrival of nationals to positively affect their wages and employment.
Giovanni Peri estimated that an increase of 1% in migration flows represents a long-term increase in real wages of between 0.6 and 0.9%.
And, without taking into account the fact that the diversity contributed by immigrants contributes to the creation of ideas and economic growth (there is a large proportion of naturalized American Nobel prizes and companies such as Google, Intel, Paypal, eBay and Yahoo were founded by immigrants).
Immigrants are also net contributors to social systems, as they contribute on average 1% of the total budget in European countries.
