In this poor region, the association is experiencing rapid success.
It is politicized and demands strict respect for Sharia, while its militants engage in the fight against the wicked central government.
The latter are primarily aimed at churches, bars, administrations.
In 2009, Boko Haram militants were particularly active and the attacks on the police stations multiplied.
Abuya’s reaction was, as usual, widespread.
The army attacked the city and 800 people were killed.
Mohammed Yusuf, who was arrested alive, is sentenced to death in prison.
